headline: What Enterprise Products Partners (EPD)'s $6 Billion Expansion and Dividend Strength Means for Shareholders
summary: Enterprise Products Partners recently attracted increased attention after completing US$6 billion in growth capital projects, including the acquisition of a natural gas gathering affiliate from Occidental Petroleum and plans for a new gas processing facility to support further expansion. Analysts have highlighted the company’s robust dividend yield above 7% and almost three decades of distribution increases, underscoring its appeal for income-focused investors as expectations of lower...
